{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow legal professionals to conduct litigation without being solicitors",
        "additional_details": "We ask the Government to create a pathway under the Legal Services Act 2007 that allows experienced legal professionals, such as paralegals and non-solicitor fee earners to obtain litigation rights. This would apply where individuals can demonstrate substantial, relevant experience, good character  and competence.\r\nThis could be achieved either by:\r\n*Alternative authorisation routes for non-solicitors via the SRA or another regulator or;\r\n*Expand the definition of \u201cauthorised person\u201d under the Act.",
        "background": "Amend the Legal Services Act 2007 to recognise experienced legal professionals (e.g., paralegals or fee earners with 10+ years' experience) as eligible to conduct litigation without requiring full solicitor authorisation.",
